HEADWORD: Upsetting
<hw>Up*set"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Conceited; assuming; <as>as, an <ex>upsetting</ex>
fellow</as>.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>such as to disturb the self-possession of;
unnerving; causing mental distress; <as>as, the sight was an
<ex>upsetting</ex> experience</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upsetting thermometer</ent>⟦br⟧
